Heat oil in large nonstick skillet on medium-high heat. Add chicken; sprinkle with 1/4 tsp. each of the garlic powder and rosemary. Cover. Cook 4 minutes on each side or until chicken is cooked through. Remove chicken from skillet. Add broth and water to skillet; stir. Bring to boil. Stir in rice and remaining garlic powder and rosemary. Top with chicken; cover. Cook on low heat 5 minutes. Remove from heat. Let stand 5 minutes.